Common Interview Questions

What is a URL?

A URL (Uniform Resource Locator) is the address used to locate a resource on the Internet.

---

What is the difference between a domain and a subdomain?

A domain identifies the main website.

A subdomain provides a separate service under the same domain.

Example:

```text
mail.google.com
```

Domain:

```text
google.com
```

Subdomain:

```text
mail
```

---

What are query parameters?

Query parameters send additional information to the server through the URL.

---

What is the default port for HTTPS?

443

---

Does the fragment reach the server?

No.

Fragments are processed only by the browser.

